### 2. Frontend — Complete Redesign

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/mdfai/OneDrive/Desktop/deep%20fake%20video/deep%20fake%20video/templates/index.html)

Full rewrite of `index.html` — pure HTML + CSS + vanilla JS, no external frameworks (except Google Fonts + Font Awesome icons via CDN). Features:

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Dark glassmorphism design | CSS backdrop-filter, gradients, HSL palette |
| Hero section | Animated gradient headline, tagline |
| Drag-&-drop upload zone | JS drag events + file input |
| Video preview | `<video>` tag updated via `URL.createObjectURL()` before upload |
| Loading overlay + spinner | CSS keyframe spinner, shown on form submit |
| Result card (REAL / FAKE) | Color-coded (green/red glow), animated entrance |
| Confidence bar | CSS `width` transition animated from 0 → value% |
| Processing details | Time taken + frames analyzed badges |
| Insight blurb | Contextual text explaining the result |
| Responsive layout | CSS Grid + media queries |
| Micro-animations | Hover lifts, fade-ins, pulse on result icon |

The template will use Jinja2 to receive the `data` variable from Flask and render the result inline (no separate AJAX call needed, keeping backward compatibility with the existing POST flow).

**Optionally** also wire up a JavaScript `fetch()` call so results appear without full page reload (progressive enhancement).

